An administrator:
    Maintain any system data: Closure dates for each academic year, staff details.
A Quality Assurance Manager:
    Oversee the process
    Can add and delete categories at any time
    Be able to download all the data after the final closure date in a CSV file for transfer out of the system.  Any uploaded documents need to be downloaded in a ZIP file.
A QA Coordinator: controll each department
Staff (everyone in system): 
    Submit one or more ideas
    Must agree to Terms and Conditions before they can submit
    Optionally upload documents to support their ideas
    Can see all submitted ideas and can comment on any idea
    Can give the Thumbs Up or Thumbs Down for any idea

Ideas:
    Can be categorised (tagged) from a list of categories
    Can be posted anonymously
    Are disabled after a closure date for new ideas
Comments:
    Can be posted anonymously 
    Can continue to be done until a final closure date

Features:
    Once an idea is submitted the system emails a notification to the Departmentâ€™s QA Coordinator
    The author of an idea receives an automatic email notification whenever a comment is submitted to any of their ideas
    Lists of Most Popular Ideas (+1 for Thumbs Up, -1 for Thumbs Down), Most Viewed Ideas, Latest Ideas and Latest Comments must be made available to all users.
    Lists of Ideas need to be paginated (5 per page)

Statistical analysis: ? Role
    Number of ideas made by each Department.
    Percentage of ideas by each Department.
    Number of contributors within each Department
    Exceptions:
        Ideas without a comment.
        Anonymous ideas and comments.




